\section{Companion simp lemmas + abstract LES specialisation (iter-029)}
\label{sec:Cohomology_MayerVietoris_iter029}

Iter-029 appends six companion declarations to Section~\ref{sec:Cohomology_MayerVietoris_iter028} (or rather, to the same Lean section \lstinline{section AffineCoverMVSquare}, immediately after $\toMayerVietorisSquare$). They are the natural follow-on to iter-028: the four corner-identification $\mathtt{simp}$ lemmas materialising Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_corners} as named, $\mathtt{simp}$-tagged lemmas, plus a sheaf-parameterised specialisation of the abstract MV-LES sequence and exactness theorem (iter-022/iter-026) to the bundled $\AffineCoverMVSquare$ data. The plan-agent has probe-verified all six declarations together against the post-iter-028 file with $\{\text{success: true, diagnostics: []}\}$.

\subsection{Why this is the natural iter-029 target}

The iter-028 close gives us the bundled $\AffineCoverMVSquare$ structure with the abstract-MV-square accessor; iter-030+ Serre-finiteness work will need (a) named $\mathtt{simp}$ lemmas for the four corners (so that downstream $\mathtt{simp}$ calls can rewrite $S.\toMayerVietorisSquare.\toSquare.X_j$ to the underlying $U_1$, $U_2$, $U_1 \sqcap U_2$, $\top$), and (b) an LES specialisation that takes a generic $\AffineCoverMVSquare\,X$ and a generic sheaf $F$, returning the $5$-term Mayer-Vietoris sequence and its exactness witness. Both are routine specialisations of the iter-022/iter-026 abstract API; the one piece of substantive content is the $X_4 = \top$ identification, which uses the $\cover$ field of $\AffineCoverMVSquare$ and is therefore the only non-$\rfl$ corner identification.

The LES specialisation is parameterised over a generic sheaf $F$ rather than specialising to $\toModuleKSheaf\,C$ directly, so that downstream consumers can reuse it across different sheaf flavours (the structure sheaf, the relative differentials sheaf, etc.). The $\toModuleKSheaf$-specific application is iter-030+ work.

\begin{lemma}[Corner identification, $X_1$, iter-029]
  \label{lem:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_X1}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.toMayerVietorisSquare_toSquare_X₁}
  \uses{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_toMayerVietorisSquare}
  In the setting of Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_toMayerVietorisSquare},
  $S.\toMayerVietorisSquare.\toSquare.X_1 = S.U_1 \sqcap S.U_2$.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  By $\rfl$ (the Mathlib $\Opens.\mayerVietorisSquare$ constructor sets $X_1 := U_1 \sqcap U_2$ definitionally).
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[Corner identification, $X_2$, iter-029]
  \label{lem:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_X2}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.toMayerVietorisSquare_toSquare_X₂}
  \uses{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_toMayerVietorisSquare}
  In the same setting, $S.\toMayerVietorisSquare.\toSquare.X_2 = S.U_1$.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  By $\rfl$.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[Corner identification, $X_3$, iter-029]
  \label{lem:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_X3}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.toMayerVietorisSquare_toSquare_X₃}
  \uses{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_toMayerVietorisSquare}
  In the same setting, $S.\toMayerVietorisSquare.\toSquare.X_3 = S.U_2$.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  By $\rfl$.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[Cover-totality identification, $X_4$, iter-029]
  \label{lem:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_X4}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.toMayerVietorisSquare_toSquare_X₄}
  \uses{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_toMayerVietorisSquare}
  In the same setting, $S.\toMayerVietorisSquare.\toSquare.X_4 = \top$.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  Direct: $S.\toMayerVietorisSquare.\toSquare.X_4 = S.U_1 \sqcup S.U_2$ holds by $\rfl$ from $\Opens.\mayerVietorisSquare$, and $S.U_1 \sqcup S.U_2 = \top$ is exactly the field $S.\cover$.
\end{proof}

All four corner lemmas above carry the $\mathtt{simp}$ attribute so that downstream $\mathtt{simp}$ calls can rewrite the abstract MV-square's corner accessors to the underlying cover data.

\begin{definition}[Mayer-Vietoris LES sequence on a 2-affine cover, iter-029]
  \label{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.HModule'_sequence}
  \uses{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_toMayerVietorisSquare, def:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence}
  Let $k$ be a field, $X : \Scheme.\{u\}$, $S : X.\AffineCoverMVSquare$, $F : \Sheaf\,(\Opens.\grothendieckTopology\,X.\toTopCat)\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$, and $n_0, n_1 : \mathbb N$ with $n_0 + 1 = n_1$. The 5-term Mayer-Vietoris LES sequence on $S$, valued in $\AddCommGrpCat$, is
  \[
    S.\HModulePrimeSeq\,k\,F\,n_0\,n_1\,h \,:=\, \HModulePrimeSeq\,k\,S.\toMayerVietorisSquare\,F\,n_0\,n_1\,h.
  \]
\end{definition}

This is a routine specialisation of the iter-022 abstract sequence to the bundled cover data; the body is a one-liner.

\begin{theorem}[Mayer-Vietoris LES exactness on a 2-affine cover, iter-029]
  \label{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence_exact}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.HModule'_sequence_exact}
  \uses{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence, thm:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence_exact}
  In the setting of Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_sequence}, the sequence $S.\HModulePrimeSeq\,k\,F\,n_0\,n_1\,h$ is exact.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
  By Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence_exact} applied to the abstract MV-square $S.\toMayerVietorisSquare$ and the sheaf $F$.
\end{proof}

\subsection{Use in Serre finiteness}

The iter-029 lemmas materialise Step 1 (the LES) and Step 2 (the cover-totality identification) of the iter-028 Serre-finiteness sketch (Section~\ref{sec:Cohomology_MayerVietoris_iter028}). The remaining work — Step 3 (affine vanishing $H^{>0}(\Spec A, \mathcal F) = 0$) and Step 4 (finiteness of each $H^0$ piece, hence of $H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$) — is iter-030+. The next iteration will probe Mathlib for affine-vanishing API state and either invoke it directly or build the necessary primitive.

